1
00:00:26,450 --> 00:00:27,770
[Team Leader Baek Su Jeong]

2
00:00:27,770 --> 00:00:30,410
[Mun Ka Young]

3
00:00:31,880 --> 00:00:33,080
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

4
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:35,970
[Choi Hyun Wook]

5
00:00:35,970 --> 00:00:37,700
[Yongsung's successor. New chaebol director?]

6
00:00:39,970 --> 00:00:42,010
[Im Se Mi]

7
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:44,740
[Kwak Si Yang]

8
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:59,130
[My Dearest Nemesis]

9
00:00:59,130 --> 00:01:00,970
[This drama is fiction.]

10
00:01:00,970 --> 00:01:03,790
[Characters and settings are fictitious.]

11
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:06,890
What's the name of the business?

12
00:01:06,890 --> 00:01:09,030
It might be a place I know.

13
00:01:09,030 --> 00:01:10,970
You probably don't.

14
00:01:10,970 --> 00:01:12,410
I wonder if it's because it's out of the way.

15
00:01:12,410 --> 00:01:13,910
For some reason, they don't get customers.

16
00:01:13,910 --> 00:01:15,030
But the food is good.

17
00:01:15,030 --> 00:01:16,860
Are you sure?

18
00:01:16,860 --> 00:01:18,950
I have a very high standard.

19
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:22,210
Eat at home, then. I'll go alone.

20
00:01:23,930 --> 00:01:25,910
Let's give it a shot.

21
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,340
I can do it myself.

22
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:56,100
How hard did you try to defeat me?

23
00:01:57,220 --> 00:02:00,320
I can say the same to you.

24
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,260
All done.

25
00:02:21,210 --> 00:02:22,690
Oh, my gosh. Oh, no...

26
00:02:22,690 --> 00:02:24,720
Hurry, hurry.

27
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:35,610
- Unni, I'm in the front-
- Don't come.

28
00:02:36,330 --> 00:02:39,160
- What?
- Don't come.

29
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:41,590
Black Dragon is here.

30
00:03:03,310 --> 00:03:04,680
What are you doing?

31
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,280
Well...

32
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:08,430
At the shop, there is...

33
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:09,920
Black...

34
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:11,440
Black?

35
00:03:12,810 --> 00:03:14,280
Dark history.

36
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:16,800
The one who scammed me in a video game.

37
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,730
He's created the darkest history of my life.

38
00:03:18,730 --> 00:03:20,620
I can't visit him myself.

39
00:03:20,620 --> 00:03:22,250
That's why you ran?

40
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:24,610
You're acting like a scammer yourself.

41
00:03:24,610 --> 00:03:26,170
Use this opportunity to teach him a lesson.

42
00:03:26,170 --> 00:03:27,330
Let's go.

43
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:29,960
I can't. My first love-

44
00:03:33,670 --> 00:03:35,410
He's my first love.

45
00:03:35,410 --> 00:03:37,140
He's not just a scammer.

46
00:03:37,140 --> 00:03:38,710
I don't ever want to see him again.

47
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:40,620
I'd hate to see him.

48
00:03:41,810 --> 00:03:44,960
I understand how that feels, too.

49
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,440
I do, but...

50
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:49,250
this pose is a bit...

51
00:03:52,820 --> 00:03:54,190
Sorry.

52
00:03:54,190 --> 00:03:56,470
I didn't mean to do that.

53
00:03:57,220 --> 00:03:58,470
I thought it was a wall.

54
00:03:58,470 --> 00:04:00,220
Why is your chest so...

55
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:02,400
solid?

56
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,020
Did you work out instead of working?

57
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:06,330
I do both, of course.

58
00:04:06,330 --> 00:04:09,790
Go ahead and compare me to the wall.

59
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:11,750
- Enough is enough.
- Enough?

60
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:14,220
That word isn't in my vocabulary.

61
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:16,960
Will you keep hiding, then?

62
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:19,020
What if I went there and ran into him?

63
00:04:19,020 --> 00:04:21,250
- What does he look like?
- Pardon?

64
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:24,320
I need to know so we avoid him.

65
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,480
I don't know.

66
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,990
I saw him briefly when he was so young.

67
00:04:27,990 --> 00:04:30,000
His face must've changed a lot.

68
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,760
Maybe you won't recognize him, then.

69
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,330
You're right.

70
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:41,880
Someone was walking by earlier.

71
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,400
Did he leave?

72
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:48,580
So, Black Dragon is Su Jeong's director?

73
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,860
Oh, my goodness...

74
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:54,620
Wow!

75
00:04:54,620 --> 00:04:56,200
[Episode 5]

76
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:58,940
I can take a bus from here.

77
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:01,300
I'll get going, then.

78
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:28,340
I thought you were going to the office.

79
00:05:28,340 --> 00:05:30,480
Which bus are you taking?

80
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:33,580
No. 770.

81
00:05:34,450 --> 00:05:36,440
Will you wait with me?

82
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,390
I'm sure it'll be here soon.

83
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,860
I won it at the arcade.

84
00:06:06,860 --> 00:06:09,030
I know you like this character.

85
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:22,790
What? Is it too touching?

86
00:06:22,790 --> 00:06:26,420
I suppose. Who else would give you a gift but me?

87
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:28,890
You don't have to be so thankful.

88
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:37,550
It's not that.

89
00:06:39,310 --> 00:06:41,860
Can't you just tell?

90
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:43,970
It's obviously fake.

91
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:45,900
You people just don't get it.

92
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:48,420
And this isn't just a character. It's Toggaengyi.

93
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:49,580
Toggaengyi. Toggaengyi.

94
00:06:49,580 --> 00:06:51,890
He obviously has a name.

95
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,250
Forget it if you don't like it.

96
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:57,370
I'll accept it out of politeness.

97
00:07:18,790 --> 00:07:22,280
Get home safely, then.

98
00:07:23,580 --> 00:07:25,730
Okay. I'll go.

99
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:58,250
[Yongsung Department Store]

100
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:04,170
[Yongsung Food Section]

101
00:08:04,170 --> 00:08:06,560
I heard the meeting was intense yesterday.

102
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:08,690
I heard you're the only one who survived.

103
00:08:08,690 --> 00:08:10,100
Is that true?

104
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:12,020
Well, I guess...

105
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,320
- Hello.
- Hello.

106
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:31,010
As you can see, the food section

107
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:33,220
focuses on edible items.

108
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:36,130
They say it lacks diversity and approachability.

109
00:08:36,130 --> 00:08:37,940
To attract new customers,

110
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:40,670
we need popular brands from social media.

111
00:08:40,670 --> 00:08:42,650
They can't just be popular.

112
00:08:42,650 --> 00:08:45,750
They shouldn't overlap with our competitors.

113
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:47,960
So, I came up with this list of businesses.

114
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:50,730
[Yongsung Department Store Food Section Businesses]

115
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,700
Nice.

116
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,690
We can just proceed.

117
00:08:56,690 --> 00:08:57,830
Okay.

118
00:08:58,540 --> 00:09:00,620
The food section is important

119
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:02,080
for the customers and our profit.

120
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,950
It's the highlight of the renewal project.

121
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:05,740
Take extra care.

122
00:09:05,740 --> 00:09:09,300
This is where you prove your ability.

123
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:11,720
Don't disappoint me this time.

124
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:26,020
It was such an intense morning.

125
00:09:27,020 --> 00:09:28,730
So,

126
00:09:28,730 --> 00:09:32,020
why did that bastard suddenly come to the shop?

127
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,720
- The thing is-
- You said you don't see him.

128
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:35,690
You said you only talk once in a while.

129
00:09:35,690 --> 00:09:38,960
It's true. But he suddenly showed up.

130
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:41,100
Gosh, I don't know what to do, either.

131
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,530
What am I supposed to do?

132
00:09:42,530 --> 00:09:44,760
I didn't know what to do, either.

133
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:47,560
I brought the director there, but we couldn't eat.

134
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,720
I know.

135
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,610
When did you get so close to him?

136
00:09:50,610 --> 00:09:51,960
You said he was a psycho.

137
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:54,180
I suppose he isn't anymore.

138
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:56,850
Well,

139
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:58,860
as I got to know him,

140
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:02,270
he's not so bad, actually.

141
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:04,150
Not so bad?

142
00:10:05,450 --> 00:10:07,250
Listen.

143
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:10,300
Let's say Black Dragon...

144
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:15,130
became a decent person like that director.

145
00:10:15,130 --> 00:10:16,360
What would you think, then?

146
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:18,330
What? They have nothing to do with each other.

147
00:10:18,330 --> 00:10:20,200
- But what if?
- I know.

148
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:22,000
How could he become a decent person?

149
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,490
He was never good.

150
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:24,940
Even if he won the Nobel Prize,

151
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:27,770
he's still a scammer to me. Nothing changes.

152
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:29,540
Do you want to switch jobs?

153
00:10:29,540 --> 00:10:31,120
Why do you keep changing the subject?

154
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,080
Because you want him to keep coming to the shop?

155
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,070
I said I didn't make him come.

156
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:37,200
Who did, then?

157
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,510
Huh?

158
00:10:39,460 --> 00:10:40,890
How strange.

159
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:43,810
Why won't you answer me? Huh?

160
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:48,450
Yes, Director.

161
00:10:48,450 --> 00:10:51,410
You haven't changed the password yet?

162
00:10:51,410 --> 00:10:53,940
I told you to change it quickly.

163
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:55,830
Okay, got it.

164
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:59,110
Something urgent came up at work. I need to go.

165
00:10:59,110 --> 00:11:02,170
We'll talk later, okay?

166
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,680
What's the big hurry?

167
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:12,990
[Yongsung]

168
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:16,810
I dropped off your bag.

169
00:11:32,540 --> 00:11:37,230
Director, wait for me. Please?

170
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:41,020
- Are you two close?
- Ha Jin.

171
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:43,170
What are you doing here?

172
00:11:49,820 --> 00:11:51,720
I'm at work.

173
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:53,600
D-Did you come to see me?

174
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:55,950
Answer me first. Are you two close?

175
00:11:55,950 --> 00:11:57,980
Pardon? Well, yes.

176
00:11:57,980 --> 00:11:59,130
How close?

177
00:11:59,130 --> 00:12:00,420
V-Very close.

178
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:02,860
Do you know his first love, too?

179
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:05,020
Of course, I know.

180
00:12:05,020 --> 00:12:07,120
To Ju Yeon, his first love was

181
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:10,780
a loathsome curse.

182
00:12:10,780 --> 00:12:12,480
And it still is.

183
00:12:13,130 --> 00:12:16,220
I know you want to play, Ju Yeon.

184
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:18,090
The grade is what matters, right?

185
00:12:18,090 --> 00:12:19,860
You should relieve your stress on a day like today

186
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:21,500
to maintain your grades.

187
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,340
Let's play together.

188
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:25,130
What should we play? Kart?

189
00:12:25,130 --> 00:12:27,150
League? Star?
[The Legend of Fever]

190
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:31,110
I want to play that.

191
00:12:35,190 --> 00:12:36,750
[The Legend of Fever]

192
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:39,700
[Black Dragon]

193
00:12:41,580 --> 00:12:44,000
Wow, you visited me.

194
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,450
You're the best, Bbanjju.

195
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:51,200
Do I have what I asked?

196
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:54,460
Fried chicken? Plain or spicy?

197
00:12:54,460 --> 00:12:56,650
- Thank you. Have some.
- Wow!

198
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:58,380
Let's go. Let's go.

199
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:05,490
By the way, Hyung.

200
00:13:05,490 --> 00:13:06,850
Yes?

201
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:10,250
I'll...

202
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:12,410
confess my love to Strawberry.

203
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:14,880
Daebak.

204
00:13:16,550 --> 00:13:18,790
How will you tell her?

205
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:21,960
How did you do it yourself?

206
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:26,530
I've always received it. I've never done it.

207
00:13:26,530 --> 00:13:28,030
Just do it casually.

208
00:13:28,030 --> 00:13:30,350
The sincerity is more important than the method.

209
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:33,950
And you're the handsome successor of Yongsung.

210
00:13:33,950 --> 00:13:35,520
Who would say no to you?

211
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:36,960
Geez.

212
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,860
Geez, you're so shallow.

213
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:41,100
Strawberry doesn't know who I am.

214
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:44,670
She likes me for who I am.

215
00:13:45,460 --> 00:13:49,270
You need to tell me if you start going out.

216
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:52,600
I'll give you 200 won if you've dated for 22 days.

217
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:54,170
22 days?

218
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,730
This is a collect call.

219
00:14:11,730 --> 00:14:13,160
Please check the caller.

220
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,670
Bbanjju, it's Hyung. Don't hang up. Don't hang up.

221
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:17,920
- What is it?
- What do you think?

222
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:20,020
You haven't called me in a while.

223
00:14:20,020 --> 00:14:21,290
Did you...

224
00:14:21,290 --> 00:14:23,030
forget about me because you're busy

225
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:24,780
dating Strawberry?

226
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:26,980
Don't ever...

227
00:14:26,980 --> 00:14:28,370
What?

228
00:14:28,370 --> 00:14:30,700
Don't ever say that name again.

229
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,840
What? Why?

230
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:34,280
Did you get dumped by chance?

231
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:37,730
But why? You don't lack in any way.

232
00:14:37,730 --> 00:14:38,920
What's the problem?

233
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:41,280
My existence itself.

234
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:43,650
My existence itself disgusts her.

235
00:14:43,650 --> 00:14:46,670
How could she be so cruel?

236
00:14:46,670 --> 00:14:48,440
You shouldn't call me anymore, either.

237
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,710
I won't do anything silly anymore.

238
00:14:51,710 --> 00:14:54,640
Hey, hey, Bbanjju. Don't hang up. Don't.

239
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:58,660
That's probably when it started.

240
00:14:59,430 --> 00:15:02,190
He was acting his age briefly, but

241
00:15:02,190 --> 00:15:03,860
he started only focusing on

242
00:15:03,860 --> 00:15:06,320
becoming the perfect successor.

243
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:08,690
A chaebol successor?

244
00:15:08,690 --> 00:15:11,320
[Sulo]
I'm glad he wasn't an alien or a thug.

245
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,810
Excuse me?

246
00:15:12,810 --> 00:15:14,340
Anyway,

247
00:15:14,340 --> 00:15:17,120
that's how hurt he was by his first love.

248
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,930
So, why did he lie about his age?

249
00:15:18,930 --> 00:15:21,180
I was shocked to see him at the meeting.

250
00:15:21,180 --> 00:15:23,500
I know he lied about his age,

251
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,250
but his existence itself is disgusting?

252
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:26,760
That's too harsh.

253
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,740
I would've gotten hurt, too.

254
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:31,190
That's how upset she was, okay?

255
00:15:31,190 --> 00:15:34,090
What she did was still bad.

256
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:37,060
Gosh.

257
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:41,210
Who's the actual bad person?

258
00:15:41,210 --> 00:15:42,550
Do you mean Ju Yeon is?

259
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:44,830
You think it's Su Jeong, then?

260
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:47,850
Whatever.

261
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:50,210
They won't see each other again, anyway.

262
00:15:50,210 --> 00:15:52,580
Of course, if they do,

263
00:15:52,580 --> 00:15:55,280
I'm sure he wouldn't forgive someone

264
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:57,540
who left a blemish on his life.

265
00:15:57,540 --> 00:16:01,010
He'll try to ruin her future, no matter what.

266
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:04,160
For one, she won't be able to live in this country.

267
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:05,290
No.

268
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:09,480
Will he kick her out of the company first?

269
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:12,030
He's so cutthroat and scary.

270
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:14,140
She won't be able to handle it.

271
00:16:15,230 --> 00:16:17,730
Why are you so shocked?

272
00:16:18,970 --> 00:16:20,220
Was that too scary?

273
00:16:20,220 --> 00:16:22,070
Su Jeong is the scary one.

274
00:16:22,070 --> 00:16:24,000
As far as I understand, she'll try to

275
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:27,190
repay him for the shame and humiliation.

276
00:16:27,190 --> 00:16:28,930
"Eye for an eye, tooth for a tooth"

277
00:16:28,930 --> 00:16:31,070
is her life's motto.

278
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:33,870
Will Su Jeong have to leave the country?

279
00:16:33,870 --> 00:16:38,100
Ju Yeon might have to leave the planet.

280
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:39,720
If so,

281
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:42,610
are you saying...

282
00:16:42,610 --> 00:16:46,500
Su Jeong is as intense as Ju Yeon?

283
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:49,160
As far as I understand her,

284
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:50,730
yes.

285
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:55,800
I'm so glad they'd never see each other.

286
00:16:55,810 --> 00:16:58,110
What if they do?

287
00:16:58,110 --> 00:16:58,810
Pardon?

288
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:01,760
What if they already see each other every day?

289
00:17:43,090 --> 00:17:44,630
Let's see...

290
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:03,860
Wait, you've been talking about Team Leader Baek?

291
00:18:03,860 --> 00:18:05,380
The Director Killer?

292
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:08,450
Why are they so quiet, then?

293
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:12,030
- By chance-
- Yes.

294
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:14,430
They don't recognize each other.

295
00:18:14,430 --> 00:18:17,040
Wow. That's a relief.

296
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:19,780
I suppose it did happen so long ago.

297
00:18:19,780 --> 00:18:21,060
They only met briefly, too.

298
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:22,830
It's too soon to feel relieved.

299
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:26,100
They grew close, and something is up between them.

300
00:18:26,110 --> 00:18:27,420
What if they grow closer and

301
00:18:27,420 --> 00:18:29,500
develop feelings for each other?

302
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:32,390
And if they find out the truth later...

303
00:18:33,570 --> 00:18:37,330
[Yongsung successor criticized for unjust dismissal]

304
00:18:37,330 --> 00:18:39,860
[Employee planted an explosive in Yongsung Department Store]

305
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,340
- How awful!
- How awful!

306
00:18:42,340 --> 00:18:43,900
We need to tear them apart.

307
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:45,930
They can never recognize each other. Never.

308
00:18:45,930 --> 00:18:47,400
Yes.

309
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:11,980
What are you doing right now?

310
00:19:11,980 --> 00:19:13,820
What? We need to go up fast.

311
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:16,110
You can't even waste a second.

312
00:19:20,220 --> 00:19:22,470
By the way, you know Ms. Baek?

313
00:19:22,470 --> 00:19:24,050
I looked into her a bit further.

314
00:19:24,050 --> 00:19:26,040
Why do something so useless?

315
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:28,190
I said you can stop.

316
00:19:28,190 --> 00:19:30,820
I thought I wasn't thorough enough then.

317
00:19:30,820 --> 00:19:32,260
So, I looked into her further.

318
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:35,740
She seems more dogged and intense than I thought.

319
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:37,570
Wouldn't it be difficult to work with her?

320
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:40,750
That's why you said she'd be a good match for me.

321
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:43,100
There was another issue.

322
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:46,630
Looks like she's interested in someone at work.

323
00:19:47,580 --> 00:19:49,060
She's interested in someone?

324
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:51,660
Yes, she is, apparently.

325
00:19:51,660 --> 00:19:53,900
I know you despise office romance.

326
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:57,290
You warned me not to date anyone at work.

327
00:19:57,290 --> 00:20:00,090
I'm asking if that'd still be okay.

328
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,930
I'm not sure.

329
00:20:16,890 --> 00:20:19,320
She's interested in someone?

330
00:20:22,170 --> 00:20:25,690
Could it be me?

331
00:20:27,180 --> 00:20:29,350
That won't be good.

332
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:39,090
[Sulo]

333
00:20:53,260 --> 00:20:55,040
Unni.

334
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:57,830
You came. Where would you like to sit?

335
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,410
Su Jeong.

336
00:21:09,340 --> 00:21:10,930
[Hot spot to pick up a date!]

337
00:21:10,930 --> 00:21:12,910
[Men get free drinking food.]

338
00:21:21,550 --> 00:21:23,910
Gosh, I guess you can't sit here.

339
00:21:23,910 --> 00:21:25,960
I'll move if someone comes.

340
00:21:27,470 --> 00:21:30,360
So, what did you want to tell me?

341
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:35,440
You aren't introducing me to those men, right?

342
00:21:36,770 --> 00:21:38,700
Nah!

343
00:21:46,730 --> 00:21:48,140
What are you doing after work today?

344
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:50,050
You'll go straight home, right?

345
00:21:50,050 --> 00:21:52,430
Don't work late. Work alone if you need to.

346
00:21:52,430 --> 00:21:54,490
Work late alone.

347
00:21:54,490 --> 00:21:56,210
What's her problem?

348
00:21:56,210 --> 00:21:58,690
Is she bored because she gets no customers?

349
00:21:58,690 --> 00:22:00,710
I thought it wasn't too bad.

350
00:22:02,090 --> 00:22:04,770
I printed a logo direction.

351
00:22:05,850 --> 00:22:08,220
Whoa, I love this one.

352
00:22:08,220 --> 00:22:11,000
This is exactly how we imagined it.

353
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,380
Yes, I know.

354
00:22:12,380 --> 00:22:14,550
It's the first round, but it's pretty good.

355
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:16,340
We don't have to change it too much.

356
00:22:16,340 --> 00:22:18,150
Whoa...

357
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:23,180
Chief Kim really is the best.

358
00:22:23,180 --> 00:22:25,760
How is he always so perfect?

359
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:27,830
I can't believe it.

360
00:22:29,060 --> 00:22:30,660
Na Na?

361
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:34,590
You're about to join his fan club, too.

362
00:22:34,590 --> 00:22:36,280
- Fan club?
- I mean...

363
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:39,300
there's a fan club for Chief Kim at work.

364
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:42,480
I think the design team's Ms. Jeong is the leader.

365
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:44,900
Is he that popular?

366
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:46,250
Of course.

367
00:22:46,250 --> 00:22:48,960
He's really cool, you know.

368
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:51,270
He's sweet, he smiles often,

369
00:22:51,270 --> 00:22:53,720
friendly, and polite.

370
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:57,430
How do you know so well? You never worked with him.

371
00:22:57,430 --> 00:23:00,090
We had coffee together once.

372
00:23:00,090 --> 00:23:02,390
He wanted to ask me something.

373
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:03,510
Just the two of you?

374
00:23:03,510 --> 00:23:05,820
That's too obvious of a move.

375
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:07,820
He could've asked me instead.

376
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:09,470
He's crazy. You're way younger.

377
00:23:09,470 --> 00:23:12,380
No, it was nothing like that.

378
00:23:12,380 --> 00:23:14,390
What did he ask you about?

379
00:23:14,390 --> 00:23:16,730
The thing is...

380
00:23:16,730 --> 00:23:21,190
he asked me about you, Team Leader.

381
00:23:21,190 --> 00:23:23,320
- Me?
- Yes.

382
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:39,440
Team Leader Baek Su Jeong,

383
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:42,080
there's a good opportunity somewhere else.

384
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:44,780
Are you interested in switching jobs?

385
00:24:09,550 --> 00:24:11,600
Geez Louise.

386
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:13,960
Get back to work.

387
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:16,740
Crazy, whoa...

388
00:24:17,670 --> 00:24:20,430
Are you free, Chief Kim?

389
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:24,860
[Yongsung Department Store]

390
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:26,860
Yes.

391
00:24:29,250 --> 00:24:30,980
Where is Team Leader Baek...

392
00:24:30,980 --> 00:24:33,740
Oh, she left earlier.

393
00:24:35,950 --> 00:24:38,470
- Good night.
- Good night.

394
00:24:38,470 --> 00:24:41,840
Maybe the Team Leader was interested in the Chief, too.

395
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:43,400
No way.

396
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:46,930
Why should he see her after work?

397
00:24:51,070 --> 00:24:53,140
What did you just say?

398
00:24:54,170 --> 00:24:55,620
W-Which part?

399
00:24:55,620 --> 00:24:58,030
Who is Team Leader Baek interested in...

400
00:24:58,030 --> 00:25:00,370
Who is she meeting with again?

401
00:25:00,370 --> 00:25:03,920
Chief Kim Sin Won from the design team.

402
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:09,020
Deputy Yang Jun Su!

403
00:25:09,790 --> 00:25:11,270
Yes.

404
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:14,060
Your top button is loose.

405
00:25:14,060 --> 00:25:17,890
Please straighten up and dress properly.

406
00:25:23,750 --> 00:25:25,410
Thank you!

407
00:25:25,410 --> 00:25:27,480
- Thank you!
- Thank you.

408
00:25:37,230 --> 00:25:39,120
We could've talked at the office.

409
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,730
Why did you invite me to a cafe?

410
00:25:40,730 --> 00:25:42,920
What a waste of time.

411
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:45,300
Well, the thing is...

412
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:48,570
I don't know where to start.

413
00:25:48,570 --> 00:25:50,660
Do you mind if I start, then?

414
00:25:50,660 --> 00:25:53,650
Of course not. Go ahead.

415
00:25:53,650 --> 00:25:55,950
Chief Kim,

416
00:25:55,950 --> 00:25:59,010
are you interested in me?

417
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:02,820
Yes.

418
00:26:02,820 --> 00:26:06,290
I can't let my employee be a victim of a rumor.

419
00:26:06,290 --> 00:26:09,210
That's why I'm going. That's why.

420
00:26:26,630 --> 00:26:28,150
It wasn't...

421
00:26:30,410 --> 00:26:32,140
me.

422
00:26:40,610 --> 00:26:42,080
I'm asking you.

423
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:44,380
Are you interested in me?

424
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:51,950
I'd be lying...

425
00:26:51,950 --> 00:26:53,630
if I said no.

426
00:26:54,550 --> 00:26:57,380
But I'm not interested in you romantically.

427
00:26:57,380 --> 00:26:59,450
What are you saying? Of course not.

428
00:26:59,450 --> 00:27:01,040
Aren't you angry at me because

429
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:03,050
you were close to the former director?

430
00:27:03,050 --> 00:27:07,320
Was it the one before? Or the one before him?

431
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:08,850
- Pardon?
- If not,

432
00:27:08,850 --> 00:27:11,950
why would you ask around about me?

433
00:27:11,950 --> 00:27:14,970
Well, I think you're very mistaken-

434
00:27:14,970 --> 00:27:16,450
No need for an excuse.

435
00:27:16,450 --> 00:27:18,320
Don't be sneaky behind my back.

436
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:20,210
Talk to me if you have a complaint.

437
00:27:20,210 --> 00:27:21,570
Instead of poking around.

438
00:27:21,570 --> 00:27:23,210
Well, then...

439
00:27:23,210 --> 00:27:24,830
Hold on. I have something to say, too.

440
00:27:24,830 --> 00:27:25,900
What is it?

441
00:27:25,900 --> 00:27:27,910
W-Well, the thing is...

442
00:27:27,910 --> 00:27:31,650
w-will you keep working for Director Ban?

443
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,350
Why would you ask that?

444
00:27:33,350 --> 00:27:34,630
Will you get me fired?

445
00:27:34,630 --> 00:27:36,720
No, there's no way.

446
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:40,300
Well, what I'm saying is...

447
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:43,280
So... w-what was I going to say?

448
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:47,090
Take care.

449
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:54,800
[He Kisses for 6,000 Won]

450
00:27:55,350 --> 00:27:57,140
[Baek Su Jeong and Kim Sin Won]

451
00:28:07,870 --> 00:28:09,630
No.

452
00:28:09,630 --> 00:28:12,380
She must have better taste than that.

453
00:28:14,490 --> 00:28:16,680
[I have an ideal type, too]

454
00:28:19,090 --> 00:28:21,860
[I appreciate the thought. Mind if I left?]

455
00:28:30,430 --> 00:28:32,140
No!

456
00:28:43,060 --> 00:28:45,000
Who's here at this hour?

457
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:47,400
Don't get up, Dad.

458
00:28:55,020 --> 00:28:57,960
I'm not signing another contract, right?

459
00:28:57,960 --> 00:29:00,570
It's not like that.

460
00:29:01,620 --> 00:29:02,890
Have some food first.

461
00:29:02,890 --> 00:29:05,120
The eggs look so tasty today, too.

462
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:07,350
I haven't had dinner yet.

463
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:13,620
I'm here to give you important advice.

464
00:29:15,310 --> 00:29:16,460
For me?

465
00:29:16,460 --> 00:29:18,880
It's important to keep work and life separate.

466
00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:22,310
But watching my employee's life get ruined

467
00:29:22,310 --> 00:29:25,170
isn't what a boss should do.

468
00:29:26,450 --> 00:29:27,800
Pardon?

469
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:32,900
Read this.

470
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:37,750
You came to recommend a cartoon?

471
00:29:37,750 --> 00:29:39,030
[He Kisses for 6,000 Won]

472
00:29:39,030 --> 00:29:42,040
I know you have no one else to talk about this-

473
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:44,140
Right there. Read that part.

474
00:29:44,140 --> 00:29:47,090
They explain why you shouldn't fall for a player.

475
00:29:47,090 --> 00:29:49,240
You said your first love was a scammer, too.

476
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:52,020
You can't be victimized by a player again.

477
00:29:52,850 --> 00:29:54,300
What are you suddenly talking about...

478
00:29:54,300 --> 00:29:58,620
I know you're romantically interested in Chief Kim.

479
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:01,530
Me?

480
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:05,040
- Aren't you?
- No.

481
00:30:05,810 --> 00:30:10,230
Then, why did you meet him at a cafe after work?

482
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:13,130
How did you know?

483
00:30:13,890 --> 00:30:17,070
I happened to see you while passing by.

484
00:30:17,070 --> 00:30:18,630
I'm disappointed.

485
00:30:18,630 --> 00:30:22,560
I didn't think you'd fall for his charm, too.

486
00:30:23,850 --> 00:30:25,340
He smiles a lot,

487
00:30:25,340 --> 00:30:28,400
he's friendly and polite. That kind of charm?

488
00:30:29,620 --> 00:30:31,850
Do you also like...

489
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:34,990
stuff like that?

490
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:38,630
No, I don't like that.

491
00:30:38,630 --> 00:30:40,320
A man should only be like that with me

492
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:42,550
even if he's a bit awkward.

493
00:30:45,390 --> 00:30:49,160
I have to agree. Love is sacred.

494
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:50,640
So, you aren't interested in Chief Kim-

495
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:52,770
I said I'm not interested.

496
00:30:52,770 --> 00:30:56,300
I asked him why he was asking around about me.

497
00:30:56,300 --> 00:30:57,780
Asking around?

498
00:30:57,780 --> 00:31:00,830
I think he's trying to find my weakness.

499
00:31:26,260 --> 00:31:28,330
Oishii*. I mean,
("Tasty" in Japanese)

500
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,820
it's tasty.

501
00:31:32,220 --> 00:31:33,850
Amazing.

502
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:37,120
Let's eat.

503
00:31:53,470 --> 00:31:56,060
Anyway, I'll enjoy it.

504
00:31:56,060 --> 00:31:58,490
Although I won't get tricked by a player.

505
00:31:58,490 --> 00:32:00,180
I'm sorry for bothering you so late.

506
00:32:00,180 --> 00:32:03,080
Tell your father I'm sorry.

507
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:04,460
Okay.

508
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,870
By the way,

509
00:32:08,870 --> 00:32:12,030
if I were actually interested in Chief Kim,

510
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:13,510
what were you going to do?

511
00:32:13,510 --> 00:32:16,120
What if I didn't care if he was a player?

512
00:32:16,120 --> 00:32:20,250
Stop you until you lose that interest.

513
00:32:21,770 --> 00:32:23,740
Why?

514
00:32:23,740 --> 00:32:26,720
Because of your duty as a boss?

515
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:28,230
I just...

516
00:32:29,230 --> 00:32:31,100
don't like it.

517
00:32:43,810 --> 00:32:45,770
I'll get going, then.

518
00:33:01,010 --> 00:33:02,660
Noona.

519
00:33:02,660 --> 00:33:04,700
Who was that just now?

520
00:33:05,530 --> 00:33:07,820
It's none of your business.

521
00:33:12,080 --> 00:33:15,170
[He Kisses for 6,000 Won]
Isn't 6,000 won cheap?

522
00:33:15,170 --> 00:33:18,120
Do you sell cartoons at the department store now?

523
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:20,310
It's not that.

524
00:33:20,310 --> 00:33:21,710
Hey, hey.

525
00:33:22,530 --> 00:33:24,310
W-What is it, then?

526
00:33:24,310 --> 00:33:26,750
Why did he come to our house again?

527
00:33:26,750 --> 00:33:28,810
I know you're an important employee, but still.

528
00:33:28,810 --> 00:33:31,030
Not only did he pay for my hospital fee,

529
00:33:31,030 --> 00:33:34,890
he keeps visiting late at night. I think...

530
00:33:37,280 --> 00:33:40,880
The director isn't interested in you, right?

531
00:33:43,630 --> 00:33:46,740
Dad, that's the funniest joke I heard recently.

532
00:33:46,740 --> 00:33:49,350
Dad, seriously. Are you a doting father?

533
00:33:49,350 --> 00:33:51,750
What man would like her?

534
00:33:51,750 --> 00:33:52,660
Hey, Baek Su Bin.

535
00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:55,360
He's young, tall, and has a nice car.

536
00:33:55,360 --> 00:33:57,500
Why would he like her?

537
00:33:59,570 --> 00:34:01,260
- I mean...
- Geez!

538
00:34:02,690 --> 00:34:04,570
Stop being annoying.

539
00:34:04,570 --> 00:34:07,150
Unless you want to crack your skull.

540
00:34:10,620 --> 00:34:12,270
Put the cup away.

541
00:34:12,970 --> 00:34:14,680
See?

542
00:34:14,680 --> 00:34:16,930
How could he be interested in her, Dad?

543
00:34:16,930 --> 00:34:18,100
Hey.

544
00:34:18,100 --> 00:34:20,720
Maybe she acts differently outside. Do you think?

545
00:34:21,850 --> 00:34:23,770
I don't think so.

546
00:34:25,500 --> 00:34:27,540
The director has an appointment today.

547
00:34:27,540 --> 00:34:29,610
So, I'll be his proxy.

548
00:34:30,420 --> 00:34:33,370
On the food section business list,

549
00:34:33,370 --> 00:34:37,240
Happy Milk replaced Ganghan Farm.

550
00:34:37,240 --> 00:34:39,320
Did the business team make the change?

551
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:40,270
Yes.

552
00:34:40,270 --> 00:34:42,340
I thought it'd be impossible to work with Ganghan Farm.

553
00:34:42,340 --> 00:34:43,850
So, I changed them out.

554
00:34:43,850 --> 00:34:45,640
They can't be replaced.

555
00:34:45,640 --> 00:34:47,610
They're very popular these days

556
00:34:47,610 --> 00:34:50,740
and he doesn't work with any department stores.

557
00:34:50,740 --> 00:34:53,480
We should have them to set our food section apart.

558
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:55,430
You think I don't know that?

559
00:34:55,430 --> 00:34:57,920
I tried convincing them.

560
00:34:57,920 --> 00:34:59,070
Even if we offered 10 billion,

561
00:34:59,070 --> 00:35:01,110
they won't join a department store.

562
00:35:01,110 --> 00:35:03,650
That's their company policy or something.

563
00:35:03,650 --> 00:35:04,770
But we should try to convince-

564
00:35:04,770 --> 00:35:06,440
It's easier said than done.

565
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:08,660
You think the business team does nothing?

566
00:35:08,660 --> 00:35:10,370
They won't even negotiate.

567
00:35:10,370 --> 00:35:12,230
How will we convince them?

568
00:35:13,060 --> 00:35:15,980
You should try it if you can.

569
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:24,890
Happy Milk is a competitive brand, too.

570
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:27,220
Got it.

571
00:35:27,220 --> 00:35:29,550
It's important to be realistic, too.

572
00:35:29,550 --> 00:35:32,980
I'll report to the Director with this list.

573
00:35:32,980 --> 00:35:34,930
Let's move on, then.

574
00:35:45,250 --> 00:35:46,140
[Ganghan Farm]

575
00:35:46,140 --> 00:35:48,150
[5 hours 34 minutes]

576
00:35:50,140 --> 00:35:52,230
Are you thinking of going there?

577
00:35:52,230 --> 00:35:56,020
You never know. Tomorrow's the weekend, too.

578
00:35:56,020 --> 00:35:58,470
All right. Good luck.

579
00:35:58,470 --> 00:35:59,960
Okay.

580
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:16,860
Bravo!

581
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:19,600
That was great.

582
00:36:20,340 --> 00:36:22,110
Nice job.

583
00:36:34,750 --> 00:36:36,690
Thank you.

584
00:36:36,690 --> 00:36:38,380
Well done.

585
00:36:38,380 --> 00:36:41,110
I don't know why they love golf.

586
00:36:41,110 --> 00:36:43,350
I wouldn't have come if it wasn't for the Chairwoman.

587
00:36:43,350 --> 00:36:45,460
But considering...

588
00:36:46,660 --> 00:36:49,250
Congratulations on hitting a hole-in-one.

589
00:36:49,250 --> 00:36:51,570
What can I say? I'm Ban Ju Yeon.

590
00:36:51,570 --> 00:36:53,810
I'm good at everything.

591
00:36:55,450 --> 00:36:58,660
Why was Ganghan Farm removed from the list?

592
00:36:58,660 --> 00:37:00,650
The business team made the decision.

593
00:37:00,650 --> 00:37:03,610
Ganghan Farm won't join a department store.

594
00:37:03,610 --> 00:37:06,730
That's why it'd be impactful if they joined us.

595
00:37:06,730 --> 00:37:08,640
Tell them to convince them somehow.

596
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:10,110
There's still time.

597
00:37:10,110 --> 00:37:14,420
Team Leader Baek left to convince them today.

598
00:37:14,420 --> 00:37:15,870
By herself?

599
00:37:15,870 --> 00:37:18,530
Although the result isn't guaranteed.

600
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:21,860
I guess it'd get resolved soon.

601
00:38:20,500 --> 00:38:22,420
I'll carry it to your destination.

602
00:38:22,420 --> 00:38:24,560
No, no. It's heavy.

603
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:26,570
I'm going all the way to the farm.

604
00:38:26,570 --> 00:38:29,600
I'll carry it for you because it's heavy.

605
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:33,140
What a nice young lady. Thank you.

606
00:38:33,140 --> 00:38:36,580
By the way, why did you come this far alone?

607
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:40,700
Well, I'm visiting the farm. The Ganghan Farm.

608
00:38:40,700 --> 00:38:43,420
I hear their ice cream is amazing.

609
00:38:43,420 --> 00:38:45,020
But they only sell it here.

610
00:38:45,020 --> 00:38:47,540
I wanted to try it and check out the farm, too.

611
00:38:47,540 --> 00:38:49,960
Gosh. You must have a lot of free time.

612
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:53,030
Why come this far for just ice cream?

613
00:38:53,030 --> 00:38:54,620
I know.

614
00:38:54,620 --> 00:38:56,170
I wish they joined

615
00:38:56,170 --> 00:38:59,350
a department store so people could try it easily.

616
00:38:59,350 --> 00:39:02,990
Tasty food is tastier when you share, they say.

617
00:39:07,780 --> 00:39:09,980
W-What's wrong?

618
00:39:12,390 --> 00:39:13,790
Give me that.

619
00:39:13,790 --> 00:39:16,060
G-Give me that.

620
00:39:16,930 --> 00:39:19,320
You got me, CEO An.

621
00:39:20,170 --> 00:39:21,530
[CEO An Jae Suk]

622
00:39:27,300 --> 00:39:28,580
Which corporation are you from?

623
00:39:28,580 --> 00:39:31,100
KEO or Yongsung?

624
00:39:31,100 --> 00:39:33,780
I'm from Yongsung's strategy team.

625
00:39:33,780 --> 00:39:36,180
My name is Baek Su Jeong. Nice to meet you.

626
00:39:36,180 --> 00:39:37,930
No need to greet me.

627
00:39:37,930 --> 00:39:41,140
You think I'd sell my product through Yongsung?

628
00:39:41,140 --> 00:39:44,790
I hate nothing more than greedy chaebol.

629
00:39:44,790 --> 00:39:46,320
Chaebol.

630
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:49,370
So, will you reject...

631
00:40:11,540 --> 00:40:14,830
This way, CEO An.

632
00:40:15,890 --> 00:40:17,750
What's this now?

633
00:40:18,750 --> 00:40:20,070
Seeing how you present yourself,

634
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:22,890
you don't look like a regular employee.

635
00:40:22,890 --> 00:40:24,590
Of course not. I'm Yongsung's successor-

636
00:40:24,590 --> 00:40:27,210
He's my little brother who was...

637
00:40:30,110 --> 00:40:32,250
sponsored by Yongsung.

638
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:35,060
This fancy young man is?

639
00:40:36,060 --> 00:40:39,240
You're mistaken because of his car and outfit.

640
00:40:39,240 --> 00:40:41,320
He's a driver.

641
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:44,640
He doesn't own the car or outfit.

642
00:40:44,640 --> 00:40:46,310
You said you were nearby.

643
00:40:46,310 --> 00:40:49,090
You came to see your sister here.

644
00:40:49,090 --> 00:40:51,000
This is great, CEO An.

645
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,860
We'll drive you to the farm. Get in.

646
00:40:52,860 --> 00:40:54,750
No. Give me that. Give me.

647
00:40:54,750 --> 00:40:56,030
N-No...

648
00:40:56,030 --> 00:40:57,500
The bag is already in there.

649
00:40:57,500 --> 00:40:59,190
Get in, CEO An.

650
00:40:59,190 --> 00:41:01,570
Careful. Careful.

651
00:41:03,100 --> 00:41:06,000
What are you doing? Drive us.

652
00:41:11,160 --> 00:41:12,670
What the heck?

653
00:41:14,860 --> 00:41:17,500
Why did you come all the way here?

654
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:19,790
Leave. I can manage it myself.

655
00:41:20,470 --> 00:41:22,520
Are you that upset that I came?

656
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:26,610
Ms. Ah hates chaebols like you.

657
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:30,230
Let's see how good you are on your own.

658
00:41:30,230 --> 00:41:32,940
I came to help you.

659
00:41:34,340 --> 00:41:37,150
You came to help me?

660
00:41:37,150 --> 00:41:40,350
No need to find it touching.

661
00:41:41,350 --> 00:41:43,880
You came because you doubted my ability?

662
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:46,160
You didn't think I could do it on my own?

663
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:47,670
I think you can.

664
00:41:47,670 --> 00:41:49,270
You'll do a good job.

665
00:41:50,130 --> 00:41:51,470
But?

666
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:55,280
But it's hard to work alone.

667
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:57,010
It's lonely, too.

668
00:42:00,110 --> 00:42:02,180
It's okay if you don't need me.

669
00:42:05,580 --> 00:42:08,550
Okay. Let's convince her together.

670
00:42:08,550 --> 00:42:10,200
But keep pretending to be my brother.

671
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:11,440
Don't let her know you're a chaebol.

672
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:13,570
Why a little brother?

673
00:42:13,570 --> 00:42:14,950
What should I have said, then?

674
00:42:14,950 --> 00:42:17,160
A friend sounds weird. A boyfriend is even worse.

675
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:18,290
Why is that weird?

676
00:42:18,290 --> 00:42:19,390
It is.

677
00:42:19,390 --> 00:42:21,650
I'm obviously much older.

678
00:42:21,650 --> 00:42:23,290
A boyfriend could be younger.

679
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:24,470
If that's the case,

680
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:26,850
isn't it weirder that your boss is younger?

681
00:42:27,560 --> 00:42:31,080
Stop talking nonsense and look for CEO An.

682
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:33,770
She... she just went that way earlier.

683
00:42:34,640 --> 00:42:37,360
Why does he keep confusing me?

684
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:42,520
What's nonsense?

685
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:51,770
♫ To be honest, I don't know, oh, no ♫

686
00:42:51,770 --> 00:42:53,940
♫ I think I'm losing my mind ♫

687
00:42:53,940 --> 00:42:55,530
♫ Oh, my gosh ♫

688
00:42:55,530 --> 00:42:56,680
♫ Like this ♫

689
00:42:56,680 --> 00:42:58,270
♫ What to do? ♫

690
00:42:58,270 --> 00:42:59,290
♫ I don't know ♫

691
00:42:59,290 --> 00:43:01,140
♫ Something made me cry ♫

692
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:04,270
♫ Destiny is playing tricks ♫

693
00:43:04,270 --> 00:43:07,020
♫ It's like magic ♫

694
00:43:07,770 --> 00:43:09,970
♫ Maybe we are ♫

695
00:43:09,970 --> 00:43:11,760
What's this now?

696
00:43:13,690 --> 00:43:15,040
CEO An!

697
00:43:15,830 --> 00:43:18,910
♫ Shine a light on my heart ♫

698
00:43:18,910 --> 00:43:20,390
Sweetie.

699
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:24,190
CEO An.

700
00:43:24,940 --> 00:43:26,660
What's this?

701
00:43:29,220 --> 00:43:31,180
Wait for us!

702
00:43:39,860 --> 00:43:41,470
It's not easy.

703
00:43:41,470 --> 00:43:42,890
Let's give up.

704
00:43:42,890 --> 00:43:45,850
We're only making us look foolish.

705
00:43:45,850 --> 00:43:47,750
No.

706
00:43:47,750 --> 00:43:48,980
We're already foolish.

707
00:43:48,980 --> 00:43:51,060
She's refusing because we're chaebols?

708
00:43:51,060 --> 00:43:53,480
Her business mindset is poor.

709
00:43:54,240 --> 00:43:55,940
Just once...

710
00:43:56,690 --> 00:43:59,820
Let's convince her just once more, please?

711
00:44:04,420 --> 00:44:06,230
This is our last time.

712
00:44:08,360 --> 00:44:09,840
Yes.

713
00:44:11,580 --> 00:44:12,900
CEO An.

714
00:44:12,900 --> 00:44:15,060
Gosh, you scared me.

715
00:44:15,060 --> 00:44:18,600
Are you determined to give me a heart attack?

716
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:20,830
Get out of my face.

717
00:44:20,830 --> 00:44:23,440
I can't do that, CEO An.

718
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:26,010
I can't give up now that I've seen the farm, too.

719
00:44:26,010 --> 00:44:29,080
I want many people to learn about your products.

720
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:30,430
I don't care.

721
00:44:30,430 --> 00:44:31,950
Leave, I said. Leave now.

722
00:44:31,950 --> 00:44:34,410
CEO An, I mean it. Let's talk for a moment-

723
00:44:34,410 --> 00:44:37,040
I have nothing to say. Get lost.

724
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:38,410
Get out of my face.

725
00:44:38,410 --> 00:44:39,910
- Get out.
- We should talk-

726
00:44:39,910 --> 00:44:41,700
Oh, hey!

727
00:44:45,370 --> 00:44:47,570
Gosh, I can't believe this.

728
00:44:47,570 --> 00:44:50,910
They're putting on a show at my farm.

729
00:44:50,910 --> 00:44:53,190
What a show this is.

730
00:45:00,590 --> 00:45:03,330
We aren't open yet.

731
00:45:04,800 --> 00:45:06,100
What brings you here at this hour?

732
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:07,830
I'm here to see you.

733
00:45:07,830 --> 00:45:10,880
- Me?
- The thing is...

734
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:12,870
I don't think I could tear them apart.

735
00:45:12,870 --> 00:45:15,960
I think we need a plan.

736
00:45:15,960 --> 00:45:18,760
You should've called first.

737
00:45:18,760 --> 00:45:21,360
I was just about to go to the market.

738
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:25,200
Really? Then, we can talk on the way, right?

739
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:26,800
Shall we?

740
00:45:33,870 --> 00:45:37,350
You're into internet novels.

741
00:45:37,350 --> 00:45:38,910
I knew it.

742
00:45:38,910 --> 00:45:41,580
I love your writing on Instagram.

743
00:45:41,580 --> 00:45:44,460
I used to read some in the army, too.

744
00:45:44,460 --> 00:45:45,780
In the army?

745
00:45:45,780 --> 00:45:49,440
Yes. Everything is fun there except the training.

746
00:45:50,210 --> 00:45:52,110
Do you still game these days?

747
00:45:52,110 --> 00:45:54,090
Sometimes.

748
00:45:54,090 --> 00:45:55,930
I played often before I opened the shop.

749
00:45:55,930 --> 00:45:58,270
But I'm too busy these days.

750
00:45:58,270 --> 00:46:01,320
I let someone else become the team leader, too.

751
00:46:01,320 --> 00:46:03,060
Why do you keep asking about me?

752
00:46:03,060 --> 00:46:05,810
You came to talk about Ju Yeon and Su Jeong.

753
00:46:05,810 --> 00:46:08,160
W-Well, yes. I did.

754
00:46:08,160 --> 00:46:10,460
That's why I'm here.

755
00:46:10,460 --> 00:46:14,090
What do we do with those two?

756
00:46:14,090 --> 00:46:17,220
They ended up in the same company.

757
00:46:17,220 --> 00:46:19,060
But I'm relieved that

758
00:46:19,060 --> 00:46:21,660
they don't see each other on weekends.

759
00:46:21,660 --> 00:46:24,060
Don't you have weekend plans, by the way?

760
00:46:24,060 --> 00:46:25,750
Is it okay to be here?

761
00:46:25,750 --> 00:46:28,080
A lot of people must want to see you.

762
00:46:31,090 --> 00:46:31,990
[Gyu Myeong]

763
00:46:33,300 --> 00:46:35,530
I'm not meeting anyone. No.

764
00:46:51,310 --> 00:46:55,240
Do you always bring the same clothes?

765
00:46:55,240 --> 00:46:56,530
Of course.

766
00:46:56,530 --> 00:46:58,910
I come prepared. Better than some people.

767
00:46:59,840 --> 00:47:01,030
But this place is too-

768
00:47:01,030 --> 00:47:04,280
You're all changed. Why don't you sit?

769
00:47:04,280 --> 00:47:08,040
CEO An, is this really your home?

770
00:47:08,040 --> 00:47:10,440
I'm worried about Ganghan Farm's finances.

771
00:47:10,440 --> 00:47:13,770
Why? What are you worried about?

772
00:47:13,770 --> 00:47:17,600
Hey, Ban Ju Yeon. Do you want to be spanked?

773
00:47:18,950 --> 00:47:21,480
- Spanked?
- She donated all of her assets

774
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:24,880
and she's been leading a frugal life. How rude.

775
00:47:24,880 --> 00:47:26,660
Go ahead and apologize.

776
00:47:27,450 --> 00:47:29,210
Rude?

777
00:47:30,930 --> 00:47:34,600
But shouldn't you live somewhere nicer?

778
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:35,990
You've worked hard.

779
00:47:35,990 --> 00:47:38,440
Why? What's wrong with my house?

780
00:47:38,440 --> 00:47:41,330
It's enough for just me.

781
00:47:41,330 --> 00:47:43,080
Stop being silly.

782
00:47:43,080 --> 00:47:45,750
Let's sit and eat.

783
00:47:47,410 --> 00:47:49,730
You'd spank me?

784
00:47:50,570 --> 00:47:52,170
It's my butt...

785
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:56,000
It's so much rice.

786
00:47:56,000 --> 00:47:57,580
It's not that much.

787
00:47:57,580 --> 00:47:59,610
That's why you're so skinny.

788
00:47:59,610 --> 00:48:02,100
Have some more afterward.

789
00:48:02,100 --> 00:48:05,110
- Okay.
- Try this, too. It's godeulbbaegi.

790
00:48:05,110 --> 00:48:07,470
It's a little bitter but tasty.

791
00:48:07,470 --> 00:48:10,570
I harvested it from the garden.

792
00:48:12,300 --> 00:48:14,140
Okay.

793
00:48:17,540 --> 00:48:20,070
What? You don't want it?

794
00:48:21,870 --> 00:48:23,640
Noona.

795
00:48:23,640 --> 00:48:27,270
Huh? D-Did you call me?

796
00:48:27,270 --> 00:48:29,910
CEO An harvested this godeulbbaegi.

797
00:48:29,910 --> 00:48:31,660
You aren't refusing to eat it, right?

798
00:48:31,660 --> 00:48:33,460
That'd be rude.

799
00:48:36,130 --> 00:48:38,250
Of course not.

800
00:48:38,250 --> 00:48:39,980
That's good, then.

801
00:48:41,380 --> 00:48:44,240
Enjoy, Noona.

802
00:48:45,380 --> 00:48:48,670
You should enjoy it, too, little brother.

803
00:48:48,670 --> 00:48:51,720
You love bitter food.

804
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:54,720
Thank you, Noona.

805
00:48:54,720 --> 00:48:57,250
You're so caring toward each other.

806
00:49:07,280 --> 00:49:10,750
Yes, yes. Aigoo, my baby.

807
00:49:10,750 --> 00:49:14,860
Yes. Of course, I'm okay. I'm fine.

808
00:49:14,860 --> 00:49:17,230
Have you eaten?

809
00:49:18,110 --> 00:49:20,450
Okay, okay. Bye.

810
00:49:20,450 --> 00:49:23,450
Okay. Talk to you later.

811
00:49:29,450 --> 00:49:31,500
That must've been your grandson.

812
00:49:31,500 --> 00:49:32,820
Yes.

813
00:49:33,840 --> 00:49:37,520
He really loves me.

814
00:49:37,520 --> 00:49:41,050
He just passed the bar exam, and he's working.

815
00:49:41,050 --> 00:49:43,980
He called on his way home.

816
00:49:43,980 --> 00:49:46,860
I don't know who he resembles, but he's smart.

817
00:49:46,860 --> 00:49:49,290
He must resemble you.

818
00:49:51,560 --> 00:49:53,580
Does he?

819
00:49:53,580 --> 00:49:55,950
You must be so proud of him.

820
00:49:55,950 --> 00:49:58,310
Of course I am.

821
00:49:59,310 --> 00:50:03,290
He was born prematurely. He used to be sick.

822
00:50:03,290 --> 00:50:06,130
Growing up healthy was enough for me,

823
00:50:06,130 --> 00:50:09,130
but he's all grown up already.

824
00:50:09,130 --> 00:50:14,200
People call me pathetic living like this.

825
00:50:14,200 --> 00:50:16,570
They think I work just to give money away,

826
00:50:16,570 --> 00:50:18,650
but I don't do that for no reason.

827
00:50:18,650 --> 00:50:22,410
A good world for the children to live in.

828
00:50:22,410 --> 00:50:25,080
I wanted to create a society like that.

829
00:50:25,080 --> 00:50:28,120
I don't want to be a rich grandma.

830
00:50:28,120 --> 00:50:31,740
I want to be a grandma they're proud of.

831
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:37,680
Your grandson must be happy.

832
00:50:39,170 --> 00:50:42,020
He's so loved by his grandmother.

833
00:50:45,340 --> 00:50:49,580
That's why you should work with Yongsung.

834
00:50:49,580 --> 00:50:52,720
Geez, you won't give up.

835
00:50:52,720 --> 00:50:55,320
I thought you were just an employee.

836
00:50:55,320 --> 00:50:58,610
How much do they pay you, anyway?

837
00:50:58,610 --> 00:51:00,720
It's not that.

838
00:51:00,720 --> 00:51:03,430
Another business will take your spot, anyway.

839
00:51:03,430 --> 00:51:08,630
I want you to make a lot of money, not anyone else.

840
00:51:08,630 --> 00:51:11,570
It'd be nice if you became more influential.

841
00:51:11,570 --> 00:51:13,840
I want to help you, too.

842
00:51:15,670 --> 00:51:17,990
How tenacious. Seriously.

843
00:51:17,990 --> 00:51:20,670
Just eat first. Let's talk later.

844
00:51:20,670 --> 00:51:22,930
You'll hear me out if I finish this, okay?

845
00:51:22,930 --> 00:51:24,000
Okay.

846
00:51:38,530 --> 00:51:40,840
Mix it in, little brother.

847
00:51:56,180 --> 00:51:58,060
This is...

848
00:52:01,070 --> 00:52:03,400
Is this a new product you're working on?

849
00:52:03,400 --> 00:52:04,490
Can I try it?

850
00:52:04,490 --> 00:52:07,160
Yes, go ahead.

851
00:52:18,420 --> 00:52:20,100
What's this?

852
00:52:20,100 --> 00:52:21,340
Is this yogurt?

853
00:52:21,340 --> 00:52:23,780
This would be a huge hit.

854
00:52:23,780 --> 00:52:25,710
Do you want to try some?

855
00:52:26,740 --> 00:52:28,960
Here.

856
00:52:28,960 --> 00:52:31,020
Drink it up. Drink it up.

857
00:52:31,020 --> 00:52:33,080
You're trying Ganghan Farm's new product.

858
00:52:33,080 --> 00:52:35,860
You should be honored.

859
00:52:39,600 --> 00:52:41,800
- This is alcohol.
- Yeah.

860
00:52:41,830 --> 00:52:44,320
That's the makgeolli I made.

861
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:48,130
I used the water from the spring up there.

862
00:52:48,130 --> 00:52:49,960
It must taste good.

863
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:54,480
How foolish.

864
00:52:55,660 --> 00:52:57,850
Foolish? How rude to talk to me that way.

865
00:52:57,850 --> 00:52:59,190
Don't yell at me.

866
00:52:59,190 --> 00:53:02,300
How will you go home, Noona?

867
00:53:03,460 --> 00:53:07,310
Well, I can take the bus back.

868
00:53:07,310 --> 00:53:09,390
You should've left already.

869
00:53:09,390 --> 00:53:11,500
The buses had stopped running already.

870
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:14,630
We'll have to call a driver.

871
00:53:15,390 --> 00:53:19,270
Driver? I thought you were a driver.

872
00:53:19,270 --> 00:53:21,720
Oh, I mean, a driving service.

873
00:53:21,720 --> 00:53:25,250
You'll pay for a ride from here to Seoul?

874
00:53:26,010 --> 00:53:27,800
Couldn't I?

875
00:53:30,090 --> 00:53:33,540
Aigoo, your dad runs a hardware store

876
00:53:33,540 --> 00:53:37,250
and paying off debt from your mom's illness.

877
00:53:37,250 --> 00:53:41,070
You said you're trying to pay off the mortgage now.

878
00:53:41,070 --> 00:53:45,460
But I guess your brother hasn't suffered enough.

879
00:53:46,840 --> 00:53:49,680
I thought you weren't listening.

880
00:53:51,570 --> 00:53:54,370
It's because he's still immature. He is.

881
00:53:54,370 --> 00:53:56,190
He's five years younger than me.

882
00:53:56,190 --> 00:53:59,300
He's a kid compared to me.

883
00:53:59,300 --> 00:54:01,180
A kid?

884
00:54:01,180 --> 00:54:03,160
How much will it cost to drive to Seoul?

885
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:05,120
Why don't you just throw money away?

886
00:54:05,120 --> 00:54:07,030
What will you do, then?

887
00:54:07,030 --> 00:54:08,610
Noona.

888
00:54:10,350 --> 00:54:11,660
What do we do?

889
00:54:11,660 --> 00:54:13,920
What do you mean what will you do?

890
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:16,030
You're sleeping over.

891
00:54:27,940 --> 00:54:31,220
The potato cooked nicely, Director.

892
00:54:32,220 --> 00:54:34,280
Am I no longer the little brother?

893
00:54:34,280 --> 00:54:37,370
Why? Do you want to call me Noona again?

894
00:54:37,370 --> 00:54:40,490
You sounded so convincing that I almost believed you.

895
00:54:43,140 --> 00:54:45,820
I'm sorry this happened.

896
00:54:45,820 --> 00:54:48,160
You should've just left.

897
00:54:49,700 --> 00:54:51,600
You call that an apology?

898
00:54:52,910 --> 00:54:56,430
It's sweet. You must love this.

899
00:54:58,640 --> 00:55:02,340
Just think of it as a vacation.

900
00:55:02,340 --> 00:55:05,660
The air is nice, and the stars are pretty.

901
00:55:12,480 --> 00:55:14,990
I was just saying that.

902
00:55:14,990 --> 00:55:18,370
But this really feels like a vacation.

903
00:55:19,560 --> 00:55:22,690
I haven't been on one this year because of work.

904
00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:26,510
Why do you work so hard

905
00:55:26,510 --> 00:55:28,220
on everything?

906
00:55:31,350 --> 00:55:34,060
When I was a kid,

907
00:55:34,060 --> 00:55:36,790
I used to dangle upside down on pull-up bars.

908
00:55:36,790 --> 00:55:41,100
But a passerby said girls shouldn't play so roughly.

909
00:55:41,100 --> 00:55:44,100
I was so annoyed by it, even as a child.

910
00:55:44,100 --> 00:55:46,810
So, I played even harder.

911
00:55:47,920 --> 00:55:49,870
One day, I went to school and

912
00:55:49,870 --> 00:55:51,250
the teacher said to give up on becoming

913
00:55:51,250 --> 00:55:52,440
the class president.

914
00:55:52,440 --> 00:55:54,960
He said I can't because my mom can't care for me.

915
00:55:54,960 --> 00:55:56,770
That's nonsense.

916
00:55:56,770 --> 00:55:58,460
You'd be the president, not her.

917
00:55:58,460 --> 00:56:00,310
I know.

918
00:56:00,310 --> 00:56:02,920
People set limits for me on their own

919
00:56:03,000 --> 00:56:06,400
and judged me. I hated it.

920
00:56:06,420 --> 00:56:10,710
So, I worked even harder when I was told no.

921
00:56:10,710 --> 00:56:12,710
I was so determined.

922
00:56:13,820 --> 00:56:17,540
I wanted to prove that I could do things.

923
00:56:17,540 --> 00:56:19,490
Do you know how that feels?

924
00:56:22,170 --> 00:56:24,050
Of course.

925
00:56:24,050 --> 00:56:27,410
You don't need others' approval,

926
00:56:28,730 --> 00:56:31,470
but I guess that's my personality.

927
00:56:31,470 --> 00:56:33,800
I want to do everything well

928
00:56:33,800 --> 00:56:36,660
and I can't stand being looked down on.

929
00:56:36,660 --> 00:56:38,600
I'm like that.

930
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:51,460
I am, too.

931
00:56:52,600 --> 00:56:55,130
I want to be acknowledged

932
00:56:55,130 --> 00:56:57,720
and do well.

933
00:56:57,720 --> 00:57:01,140
I can't stand being looked down on.

934
00:57:05,960 --> 00:57:07,640
Why are you smiling?

935
00:57:10,430 --> 00:57:15,710
I was thinking you and I are similar.

936
00:57:15,710 --> 00:57:18,390
It's funny. It makes no sense.

937
00:57:21,750 --> 00:57:24,150
Why should it not make sense?

938
00:57:24,150 --> 00:57:26,590
We have another thing in common.

939
00:57:27,810 --> 00:57:29,470
Our first loves.

940
00:57:34,010 --> 00:57:38,930
I don't ever want to run into mine, either.

941
00:57:39,950 --> 00:57:41,890
I thought...

942
00:57:42,930 --> 00:57:46,240
she'd accept me as I was.

943
00:57:47,640 --> 00:57:49,550
But it was the worst.

944
00:57:53,000 --> 00:57:56,240
We both have the worst first loves.

945
00:57:56,240 --> 00:57:58,150
Should we say cheers?

946
00:58:00,780 --> 00:58:02,180
Cheers.

947
00:59:07,620 --> 00:59:08,580
[Jin unni]

948
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:11,700
Excuse me.

949
00:59:15,720 --> 00:59:17,640
Yes, Unni.

950
00:59:17,640 --> 00:59:20,650
I'm on a business trip in Gangwon with the director.

951
00:59:21,350 --> 00:59:24,040
He's not a man. He's the same age as Su Bin.

952
00:59:24,040 --> 00:59:26,580
How could I think of him as a man?

953
00:59:35,410 --> 00:59:36,600
But still.

954
00:59:36,600 --> 00:59:39,170
Aren't you too close with the director?

955
00:59:39,170 --> 00:59:40,560
Should I not be?

956
00:59:40,560 --> 00:59:42,230
It's better than being the Director Killer.

957
00:59:42,230 --> 00:59:47,030
I don't want you to learn the uncomfortable truth.

958
00:59:47,030 --> 00:59:48,970
Uncomfortable truth?

959
00:59:48,970 --> 00:59:52,580
Well, you said he's a chaebol.

960
00:59:52,580 --> 00:59:54,170
What if he's corrupt?

961
00:59:54,170 --> 00:59:55,540
I know you can't tolerate that.

962
00:59:55,540 --> 00:59:58,530
It'd become a serious problem, then.

963
00:59:58,530 --> 01:00:00,000
Unni, are you bored?

964
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:02,740
Why are you suddenly so worried?

965
01:00:02,740 --> 01:00:03,960
Whatever.

966
01:00:03,960 --> 01:00:05,280
You definitely said

967
01:00:05,280 --> 01:00:07,280
you don't think of the director as a man.

968
01:00:07,280 --> 01:00:08,660
What?

969
01:00:09,900 --> 01:00:11,720
Yes.

970
01:00:11,720 --> 01:00:14,490
Okay. Carry on.

971
01:00:17,220 --> 01:00:19,230
What's her problem?

972
01:00:20,280 --> 01:00:21,980
How strange.

973
01:00:42,600 --> 01:00:44,260
Are you sleeping?

974
01:00:46,000 --> 01:00:48,960
He falls asleep whenever he drinks.

975
01:00:48,960 --> 01:00:51,770
Director, sleep inside.

976
01:00:51,770 --> 01:00:53,090
Okay?

977
01:00:53,890 --> 01:00:55,690
Director.

978
01:01:05,690 --> 01:01:07,740
How annoying.

979
01:01:08,810 --> 01:01:12,350
Well, I wanted to wake you up.

980
01:01:14,250 --> 01:01:16,900
Why do you keep looking down on me?

981
01:01:17,700 --> 01:01:19,670
When did I do that?

982
01:01:55,360 --> 01:01:57,020
Do you still...

983
01:02:04,520 --> 01:02:06,700
not see me as a man?

984
01:03:07,160 --> 01:03:10,650
[My Dearest Nemesis]

985
01:03:11,200 --> 01:03:14,100
[We thank Park Jeong Ja for the special appearance]

986
01:03:23,180 --> 01:03:25,150
♫ The moment I hold your hand ♫

987
01:03:25,150 --> 01:03:27,840
♫ It's all right, it's so high ♫

988
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:29,890
♫ I can't hide my feelings ♫

989
01:03:29,890 --> 01:03:32,220
♫ I'll work up my courage and tell you ♫

990
01:03:32,220 --> 01:03:34,200
♫ My first love is calling me ♫

991
01:03:34,200 --> 01:03:35,380
♫ I've been waiting ♫

992
01:03:35,380 --> 01:03:38,460
♫ It feels like I'm flying ♫

993
01:03:38,460 --> 01:03:41,160
I don't understand what the guy is thinking.

994
01:03:41,160 --> 01:03:44,580
We're in it together. Should we say cheers?

995
01:03:44,580 --> 01:03:47,710
Will you just ignore what happened last night?

996
01:03:47,710 --> 01:03:49,530
Let's ignore a mistake like that.

997
01:03:49,530 --> 01:03:52,430
Crazy. He can ignore a mistake like that?

998
01:03:52,430 --> 01:03:53,980
Are you going on a blind date?

999
01:03:53,980 --> 01:03:56,190
- Is that true?
- Why are you interested?

1000
01:03:56,190 --> 01:03:57,420
Su Jeong!

1001
01:03:57,420 --> 01:03:59,680
You're concerned about my blind date.

1002
01:03:59,680 --> 01:04:01,540
I'm not concerned.

1003
01:04:01,540 --> 01:04:03,170
What's wrong with me?

1004
01:04:03,170 --> 01:04:05,910
Why doesn't she think of me as a man?

1005
01:04:05,910 --> 01:04:10,690
♫ My heart leans toward you ♫

1006
01:04:10,690 --> 01:04:13,290
♫ I'll tell you as many times it takes ♫

1007
01:04:13,290 --> 01:04:15,210
♫ I like you... ♫
